Interface BidirectionalMap<L,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    L -
    R -
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    SimpleBidirectionalMap

    public interface BidirectionalMap<L,R>
extends java.io.Serializable
    [DELETEME_LATER: imported from BIUTEE 2.4.1. infrastructure without modification] A one-to-one mapping of elements of type L to elements of type R.
    Each element of type L in the BidirectionalMap has exactly one element of type R mapped to it.
    Each element of type R in the BidirectionalMap has exactly one element of type L mapped to it. Not thread safe, unless explicitly specified.
    Author:
    Asher Stern
    See Also:
    lava.util.Map
